transcript.text: Hello welcome to on print shop.
This video is about package master, package box weight and bulk package import package master.
Previously we have to create package for each product.
Now you can create one master package and assign it to multiple products Bulk package import.
The created master package can be assigned one by one or you can assign it to multiple products together by import option.
Package box weight.
Previously we don't have any facility to add package box weight.
So right now you will be able to add package box weight.
Let's see how to set all these in admin.
Click on store configuration.
Click on shipping method to set master package.
Click on manage master packages.
Click on Add button.
Here you can set master package and also add package box weight.
Click on save button.
Like this you can create multiple package masters.
Now we will see how to assign this master package to products.
Click on shipping method.
Select specific shipping method.
Click on action and select shipping package configuration.
Select product from drop down.
Select package.
So you will see custom and all the master packages which has been created.
For custom you need to put all values and also you can add package box weight and for master package all values will be automatically fetched from package master.
You can assign package master to 1 by 1 product.
We also have option of import where you can assign package master to multiple products together.
Click on Import Package Configuration, select Multiple products and click on download.
You can see the downloaded excel sheet and Master package column in it.
If you go to help section you can see Master package reference.
So you just need to put master packaged reference ID and you can skip all remaining fields, save the excel sheet and impart the file.
So in that way you can assign package configuration for multiple products in a single click.
Thank you.
If you have any queries please contact us at support at onprintshop com.
